channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Lawyers in Trump trial hold meeting on jury instructions
item.description: Former President Donald Trump's criminal hush money trial continues in New York. Follow here for the latest live news updates, analysis and more.

item.title: Judge hears wrongful conviction claim of Missouri inmate in prison for 33 years
item.description: Christopher Dunn has spent 33 years in prison serving life without parole for a murder in Missouri he has always claimed he didnâ€™t commit

item.title: Middle East turmoil: UN sounds alarm on Gaza aid and Iran mourns president
item.description: There is growing alarm among UN officials about the difficulty of transferring aid safely within Gaza. Meanwhile, Iran elections are set for June 28 following the death of President Ebrahim Raisi, which has further destabilized the region. Follow for live updates.

item.title: Investigation continues into Matthew Perry's death, source of ketamine: Sources
item.description: The death investigation into "Friends" star Matthew Perry remains ongoing, law enforcement sources said.

item.title: The latest on Singapore Airlines turbulence incident
item.description: One person has died and at least 71 others were injured on board a Singapore Airlines plane that encountered severe turbulence on a flight from London to Singapore. Follow for live updates.

item.title: New filings reveal details from Trump docs case, show aide moving boxes
item.description: The special counsel appears to have suspected additional efforts by former President Trump to obstruct the government's classified documents probe, according to a filing.

item.title: 'There's nothing like it,' says kayaker Dane Jackson after descending 300 feet down waterfalls
item.description: When Dane Jackson turned around and looked back at the tower of frothing water above him, he could scarcely believe what he had just experienced.

item.title: Biden releasing 1M barrels of gasoline from Northeast reserve in bid to lower prices
item.description: The sale will be allocated in increments of 100,000 barrels at a time.

item.title: May 20, 2024 Israel-Hamas war
item.description: The Biden administration denounced efforts by the International Criminal Court to seek arrest warrants for top Israeli officials and Hamas leaders, saying the court's efforts put the terrorist organization and a top US ally on equivalent footing.

item.title: It's so hot in Mexico, howler monkeys are falling dead from the trees
item.description: At least 83 howler monkeys were found dead in the Gulf coast state of Tabasco.
